Author: JPN_Trslate
Title: [ANN][Pre-ICO]☀️Setcoin☀️Revolutionary Services Marketplace Zero Comm Payment
Body: This coins seems pretty dead on almost all social media that I check.  Also, as a contractor who has completed work for them, it has been over 90 days of no payment.  They claim they have no funding, even though they started their crowd sale in Nov. 2017.   Their website seems abandoned at http://www.setcoins.io/ - when I go to click on any of the tabs, I get "entry is currently closed." I send them an email, and it bounces back.  I was able to track them down on LinkedIn and ask them what's up.  They have another website going - http://www.inserviss.com/ and claim to have offices in Los Angeles, California and Switzerland.  But even with offices in such nice locations, they still have no money to pay me for my work. My fee is a lot to me, but for an ICO it is really an insignificant amount.  If you are looking to invest in this 'opportunity,' I'd suggest otherwise.

Author: JPN_Trslate
Title: [ANN][Pre-ICO]☀️Setcoin☀️Revolutionary Services Marketplace Zero Comm Payment
Body: I don't know if this is a scam, or if they have really bad business skills.  1. They hired me as a contractor.  I completed the job.  They stated they were very happy with the work.  Then said they had no funding to pay me.  90 days and they still have no funding.  Their pre-sale started in Nov. 2017.  Their ICO sale started in March 2018.  This is month 7 of trying to raise capital, and they claim they have no money to pay for my small fee.  Scam, or really bad at business?  You tell me.   "Setcoin team creating win-win-win collaboration model between Service providers, customers and Inserviss marketplace."       lol.  What kind of company hires contractors, and not have the money to pay for the work when it is completed? This company doesn't sound like a good place to invest your hard earned money.
